						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the Chennakēśavasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Dēvarāya I, 1412 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record is damaged and is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 133[4], Nandana, Chaitra śu. 5, Monday.</hi> The date is irregular. However, if śu. 5 is a mistake for śu. 15, the details correspond to <hi rend="bold">1412 A.D., March 28, Monday.</hi></p>						

						<p>Seems to refer to the construction of the temple, the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> etc., for god Kēśavaperumāḷ by some individuals of Iṅkollu. Mentions Rāchemma-reḍḍi Anavōtānāya-reḍḍi as holding the <hi rend="italic">nāyaṅkara</hi> of Iṅkollu.</p>						

						</summary>
